-- CNA’s Mense Says Workers’ Compensation Has Been a ‘Problem Line’
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2012-03-29T14:59:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/cna-s-mense-says-workers-compensation-has-been-a-problem-line-.html
CNA Financial Corp. (CNA) , the commercial
insurer majority owned by Loews Corp., is scaling back offerings
of workers’ compensation policies after the business
underperformed other types of coverage sold by the company.  Workers’ compensation has been a “problem line,” Chief
Financial Officer Craig Mense said today at a presentation by
the Chicago-based insurer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in  New York  at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  